  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are rallying on optimism around US-Iran diplomatic efforts and potential Middle East cease-fire talks, with tech stocks pushing equities to new highs while the dollar weakens to six-week lows. Bitcoin has broken above $75K and crypto markets are showing strength, though some analysts warn of profit-taking pressure and potential fade in momentum.",
    "regimeImpact": "The geopolitical risk-off trade and broad asset rally supports the oversold relief rally thesis, but oil stability around current levels rather than falling suggests inflationary pressures remain elevated.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR ladder closely as BTC approaches potential resistance around $76K-$80K zone with German state overhang of 57K BTC creating supply risk",
      "Consider reducing short book exposure in Mature Growth names as broad tech rally and record highs suggest momentum could extend further",
      "Watch oil closely - if WTI breaks below $89 support as suggested, could signal genuine disinflationary relief supporting longer rally duration"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "BTC breaking $75K with double bottom formation targeting $82.5K suggests crypto leading risk-on sentiment",
      "Dollar at six-week lows indicates Fed independence concerns and peace dividend trades gaining traction",
      "Oil stability despite peace talks suggests structural supply concerns in Strait of Hormuz remain elevated",
      "Tech stocks hitting records while VIX likely falling suggests genuine risk appetite return rather than short covering"
    ]
